The paper deals with the encoding and decoding of combinatorial objects, specifically Hereditarily Finite Sets, Functions, and Permutations. This falls under the scope of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of tupling/untupling operations and factoradics suggests a focus on Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the application of these techniques to the construction of an executable theory of Hereditarily Finite Functions suggests a connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
